            <h6>What is an API?</h6>
            <p class="text-dark">An API <strong>(Application Programming Interface)</strong> is a software-to-software interface, not a user interface. With APIs, applications talk to each other without any user knowledge or intervention. When you buy movie tickets online and enter your credit card information, the movie ticket website uses an API to send your credit card information to a remote application that verifies whether your information is correct. Once payment is confirmed, the remote application sends a response back to the movie ticket website saying it's okay to issue the tickets.</p>
